{"abstract":[{"text":"Returns whether ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"source"},{"type":"text","text":" has been destroyed."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/source\/isdestroyed"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source\/isDestroyed"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source\/SourceProtocol-Implementations"]]},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Property","extendedModule":"GLib","symbolKind":"property","title":"isDestroyed","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"isDestroyed"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib14SourceProtocolPAAE11isDestroyedSbvp::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib6SourceC","role":"symbol"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"isDestroyed","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is important when you operate upon your objects","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"from within idle handlers, but may have freed the object","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"before the dispatch of your idle handler."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["static gboolean","idle_callback (gpointer data)","{","  SomeWidget *self = data;","   ","  g_mutex_lock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","  \/\/ do stuff with self","  self->idle_id = 0;","  g_mutex_unlock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","   ","  return G_SOURCE_REMOVE;","}"," ","static void","some_widget_do_stuff_later (SomeWidget *self)","{","  g_mutex_lock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","  self->idle_id = g_idle_add (idle_callback, self);","  g_mutex_unlock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","}"," ","static void","some_widget_init (SomeWidget *self)","{","  g_mutex_init (&self->idle_id_mutex);","","  \/\/ ...","}","","static void","some_widget_finalize (GObject *object)","{","  SomeWidget *self = SOME_WIDGET (object);","   ","  if (self->idle_id)","    g_source_remove (self->idle_id);","   ","  g_mutex_clear (&self->idle_id_mutex);","","  G_OBJECT_CLASS (parent_class)->finalize (object);","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will fail in a multi-threaded application if the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"widget is destroyed before the idle handler fires due"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to the use after free in the callback. A solution, to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this particular problem, is to check to if the source","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"has already been destroy within the callback.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"c","type":"codeListing","code":["static gboolean","idle_callback (gpointer data)","{","  SomeWidget *self = data;","  ","  g_mutex_lock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","  if (!g_source_is_destroyed (g_main_current_source ()))","    {","      \/\/ do stuff with self","    }","  g_mutex_unlock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","  ","  return FALSE;","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Calls to this function from a thread other than the one acquired by the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] the [struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] is attached to are typically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"redundant, as the source could be destroyed immediately after this function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"returns. However, once a source is destroyed it cannot be un-destroyed, so"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this function can be used for opportunistic checks from any thread.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop."}],"title":"MainContext","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Source":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GSource","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data type"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"representing an event source.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Source"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/source","kind":"symbol","title":"Source","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Source"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Source/SourceProtocol-Implementations":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source\/SourceProtocol-Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/source\/sourceprotocol-implementations","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[],"title":"SourceProtocol Implementations","kind":"article"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Source/isDestroyed":{"role":"symbol","title":"isDestroyed","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/source\/isdestroyed","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"isDestroyed"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source\/isDestroyed","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Returns whether ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"source"},{"type":"text","text":" has been destroyed."}]}}}